
Steps to preparing the HOST PC and install Yocto for LCC Low Cost Controller VDW:

1) download Ubuntu 16.04
2) download VirtualBox and setup Virtual Machine (VM)
3) install Ubuntu 16.04 in your VM
4) check that VM is connected to internet (mandatory)
5) install git with the command: sudo apt-get install git
6) clone tools repo with the command: git clone https://github.com/ROJ-ITALY/tools.git -b lcc-morty (*1)
7) change dir to tools (cd tools) and run these scripts in this order:
	a) ./download_packages
	b) ./create-yocto-environment

Steps to configuring Yocto for LCC VDW:

1) set up the right environment for the build (normal system):
	a) cd $HOME/yocto-lcc-morty
	b) MACHINE=imx6sololcc/imx6qlcc DISTRO=fsl-imx-x11 source ./fsl-setup-release.sh -b bld_lcc_normal (*2)
	c) replace the content of the file bld_lcc_normal/conf/bblayers.conf with bblayers-normal.conf
	d) replace the content of the file bld_lcc_normal/conf/local.conf with custom-local.conf

2) set up the right environment for the build (fbk system):
	a) cd $HOME/yocto-lcc-morty
	b) MACHINE=imx6sololcc DISTRO=fsl-imx-x11 source ./fsl-setup-release.sh -b bld_lcc_fbk (*2)
	c) replace the content of the file bld_lcc_fbk/conf/bblayers.conf with bblayers-fbk.conf
	d) replace the content of the file bld_lcc_fbk/conf/local.conf with custom-local.conf

---------------------	
Note:
(*1) tools dir contains some useful shell scripts in order to prepare the Host system to use Yocto Project.

(*2) You have to run this command only the first time; for the next times is sufficient enter:
		source ./setup-environment bld_lcc_normal
	or
		source ./setup-environment bld_lcc_fbk

